description:
Build the core API for generating reward signals from evaluation data.

Interface:
interface OptimizationSignal {
  trace_id: string;
  component: 'prompt' | 'retrieval' | 'tool_selection' | 'reasoning' | 'full_agent';
  signal_type: 'reward' | 'preference' | 'gradient' | 'attribution';
  value: number | PreferencePair | GradientInfo;
  metadata: Record<string, any>;
}

Files to Create:
- packages/sdk/src/optimization/signals.ts
- packages/sdk/src/optimization/types.ts
- packages/sdk/src/optimization/index.ts

Acceptance Criteria:
- Can generate reward signals from traces
- Supports multiple signal types
- Can aggregate signals from multiple sources

## Problem
Dashboard filters reset on every page reload. Users must re-apply filters each visit.

## Impact
- Annoying for repeat users
- Wastes time on every session
- Easy win that improves perceived quality

## Fix
```typescript
// Save to localStorage on filter change
useEffect(() => {
  localStorage.setItem('dashboard-filters', JSON.stringify(filters))
}, [filters])

// Load on mount
const [filters, setFilters] = useState(() => {
  const saved = localStorage.getItem('dashboard-filters')
  return saved ? JSON.parse(saved) : defaultFilters
})
```

## Effort: 1-2 hours

## Problem
useRealtime spawns individual polling intervals per run ID. With 10 active runs and WebSocket failure:
- 10 immediate API calls
- Then 10 × (3000ms polling) = cascading API calls every 3 seconds

## Location
`hooks/use-realtime.ts:214-254`

## Impact
- Excessive API calls during WebSocket failures (90% excess)
- High server load when many runs are being monitored
- Battery drain on mobile clients

## Fix
Implement single batch polling mechanism:
```typescript
const batchPolling = useCallback(async () => {
  const runIds = Array.from(subscriptionsRef.current)
  if (runIds.length === 0) return

  try {
    // Batch fetch all statuses in one request
    const statuses = await api.getBatchWorkflowStatuses(runIds)
    for (const [runId, status] of Object.entries(statuses)) {
      const update = pollToUpdate(runId, status)
      setRunStatuses(prev => new Map(prev).set(runId, update))
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.warn('Batch polling failed:', error)
  }
}, [])
```

Requires backend API endpoint for batch status fetch.

